cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and coreference resolution. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper introduces a novel deep learning architecture for resolving gendered ambiguous pronouns. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses state-of-the-art language and coreference resolution models, and introduces a new deep learning architecture. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses a deep learning architecture. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the modularity and simplicity of the architecture, which could be applicable to other NLP problems or even computer vision tasks.
